summary: This document details the forensic examination of an Apple iPad conducted by the FBI's New York CART team on September 5, 2019. The examination involved unlocking the device and performing a file system extraction, with all data being uploaded for further analysis. The document serves as a record of the technical procedures followed during the examination.

events.title: Forensic Examination of Apple iPad
events.description: The FBI's New York CART team initiated an unlock and file system extraction of an Apple iPad as part of an investigation.

locations: New York, New York, United States
keyFacts: The forensic examination was conducted on an Apple iPad 5 Model: A1823.
The device was unlocked using GrayKey v1.11.10.
A SHA256 hash was generated on the extraction file.
All extraction files were uploaded to a case volume on NYCART server systems.
The document states that it contains neither recommendations nor conclusions of the FBI.
